  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "2013-04-10", 
    "text": "Forty Hours is Full Time Act of 2013 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code, with respect to the employer mandate to provide health care coverage, to: (1) modify the formula for calculating the number of full-time employees employed by an applicable large employer subject to the mandate; and (2) define a \"full-time employee\" as an employee who is employed on average at least 40 hours per week (currently, 30 hours)."
